Dear Colleagues,
 
 
We are organizing the Visual Data mining Workshop As part of Modelling, 
Computation and Optimization in Information Systems and Management 
Sciences (MCO'08), September 8-10, 2008, Metz, France, 
(The call for paper is available on http://www.lita.univ-metz.fr/~mco08) 


To include accepted long papers in the conference proceedings, the deadline for the Visual Data mining Workshop (http://lita.sciences.univ-metz.fr/~mco08/ is extended to May 29, 2008. 
 
Due to numerous requests, we also accept abstract and short paper (4 pages) submission for presentation in the workshop, and the dead line is set to July 1st, 2008. 
Accepted abstracts and short papers will not be included in the proceedings but authors are invited to submit a long version of their work for two special issues of journals following the conference (Computational and Management Science and Computational Optimization and Applications).
 
For information, conference inscription will be 350 euros / 250 euros 
for students (proceedings + gala dinner). The workshop is considered as 
part of the conference.
 
We would be grateful if you could diffuse the call for papers (available on http://www.lita.univ-metz.fr/~mco08 ) to your 
professional networks, relationships and mailing lists.

Best regards,
 

Lydia Boudjeloud-Assala
Maître de Conférence
Université de Metz
